Others: Texas Rangers rookie Kumar Rocker struggled with his command and velocity in his home debut at Globe Life Field against the Toronto Blue Jays on September 19, 2024.
Rocker allowed two runs (one earned) on two hits, four walks, and struck out five in three innings.
He walked a batter in each of his three innings, including the leadoff batter in the second and third.
Rocker had Tommy John surgery in May 2023 after being the No. 3 overall pick in the 2022 MLB Draft.
